               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18280529-257-off1413-c1383" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-257-defend1383 t18280529-257-off1413 t18280529-257-verdict1416"></join>
         
               <p>SIXTH DAY. WEDNESDAY, JUNE 4.</p>
               <p>Second London Jury - before Mr. Common Sergeant.</p>
               <p>1336. 
               <persName id="t18280529-257-defend1383" type="defendantName">
                  CORNELIUS 
                  MARTIN
               <interp inst="t18280529-257-defend1383" type="surname" value="MARTIN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-defend1383" type="given" value="CORNELIUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-defend1383" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-defend1383" type="age" value="17"></interp>
                  </persName>
             was indicted for <rs id="t18280529-257-off1413" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-off1413" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-off1413" type="offenceSubcategory" value="pocketpicking"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18280529-257-cd1414" type="crimeDate">16th of April</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-257-off1413 t18280529-257-cd1414"></join>, 1 handkerchief, value 1s. 6d., the goods of 
                     <persName id="t18280529-257-victim1384" type="victimName">
                        Charles Harrington 
                        Twight
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-victim1384" type="surname" value="Twight"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280529-257-victim1384" type="given" value="Charles Harrington"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18280529-257-victim1384" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-257-off1413 t18280529-257-victim1384"></join>
                     </persName>
                  , from his person
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>CHARLES HARRINGTON TWIGHT. On the 16th of April, between seven and eight in the evening, I was in <placeName id="t18280529-257-crimeloc1415">Smithfield</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-257-crimeloc1415" type="placeName" value="Smithfield"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280529-257-crimeloc1415" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-257-off1413 t18280529-257-crimeloc1415"></join> inquiring my way and felt my handkerchief drawn from my pocket; I turned round, and a woman said"A man has drawn your handkerchief from your pocket;" I saw the prisoner running; I pursued and cried Stop thief! the patrol stopped him - I had not lost sight of him; he was about five or six yards from me when I first saw him; there were some persons by his side, but none between us - he ran straight forward; a little boy picked up the handkerchief - it is the one I lost.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Were you able to describe the handkerchief at the watch-house? A. Yes; I was not positive whether there were any initials on it - I said it was like one I had at home.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-257-person1385">
                  WILLIAM 
                  SPENCER
               <interp inst="t18280529-257-person1385" type="surname" value="SPENCER"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-person1385" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-person1385" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a patrol. I saw the prisoner stopped - the prosecutor was running after him; a lad gave me the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-257-person1386">
                  JOHN 
                  SPRATMAN
               <interp inst="t18280529-257-person1386" type="surname" value="SPRATMAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-person1386" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-person1386" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner running and saw him drop the handkerchief; I took it up and gave it to the officer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280529-257-person1387">
                  GEORGE 
                  GODFREY
               <interp inst="t18280529-257-person1387" type="surname" value="GODFREY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-person1387" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-person1387" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner was brought to the watch-house - the prosecutor said he thought there was some yellow in the colour of the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280529-257-verdict1416" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-verdict1416" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 17.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280529-257-punish1417" type="punishmentDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280529-257-punish1417" type="punishmentCategory" value="transport"></interp>
                     <join result="defendantPunishment" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-257-defend1383 t18280529-257-punish1417"></join>
               Transported for Fourteen Years
            </rs>.</p>
            </div1>
